gomodel:SYNGO_3820  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: [Figure 4. Syt10 Is Essential for STFP-Induced LTP of G-M Synapses]\nFigure 5. \"IGF1 Induces Rapid Postsynaptic Potentiation of G-M Synapses Requiring IGF1-R Signaling\"\n- \"The IGF1-induced potentiation of G-M IPSCs was blocked by the IGF1 receptor (IGF1-R) antagonist NVP-AEW541 (Figures 5D-5F), indicating that the synaptic potentiation was specifically caused by IGF1.\". Experimental description: \"Adult mice (age between 3 to 5 months old) with or without prior viral injections were used \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
